---
description: Project-specific rules for @siter/headless-gutenberg-react
alwaysApply: true
---

This package will become a React renderer for headless WordPress Gutenberg content.

Current phase:
- Build only the foundation.
- Create HelloWorld component.
- Do not implement full GutenbergRenderer yet.
- Do not implement WordPress fetching yet.
- Do not implement DOMPurify sanitization yet unless a later task asks for it.
- Do not implement WordPress Interactivity API yet.

Long-term architecture:
- WordPress-rendered HTML is the source of truth.
- The React package should render, sanitize and hydrate; it should not recreate Gutenberg blocks as React components.
- Generated CSS will come from `siter_headless.css_urls`.
- Wrapper class will come from `siter_headless.wrapper`.
- Interactive blocks will later load WordPress script modules from the WordPress site.

Testing:
- Use Vitest for unit tests.
- Use React Testing Library for component behavior.
- Use Playwright for playground/browser behavior.
- Use web-first Playwright assertions.

For security review of HTML rendering, CSS/script loading, or publishing changes, invoke the `security-review` skill.
For coding task quality, invoke the `coding-guidelines` skill per rule 008.
